2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:07,050
- <i>the one who drugged my wife...</i>
- Sayaka!

3
00:00:07,050 --> 00:00:08,140
You held ill will towards Sayaka.

4
00:00:08,140 --> 00:00:10,350
Ill will?

5
00:00:10,350 --> 00:00:11,950
Ridiculous.

6
00:00:11,950 --> 00:00:15,770
- The culprit is...
- Yeah.

7
00:00:15,770 --> 00:00:20,040
<i>It was her own mother, Kaori Wakamatsu.</i>

8
00:00:20,040 --> 00:00:26,240
<i>Timing and Subtitles brought to you by the</i>
🤫 <i>Secrets in Champagne</i> 🥂 <i>Team @ viki.com</i>

9
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:30,300
What will you do now?

10
00:00:31,820 --> 00:00:36,540
Will you report her actions to the police?

11
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:40,440
If only I could.

12
00:00:43,850 --> 00:00:47,250
She could very well be the culprit.

13
00:00:49,380 --> 00:00:54,080
She is the culprit.

14
00:00:54,080 --> 00:00:56,730
And she's absolutely despicable as a mother.

15
00:00:58,230 --> 00:01:04,230
But she's still Sayaka's mother.

16
00:01:06,950 --> 00:01:12,550
Sayaka doesn't know she was drugged.

17
00:01:14,260 --> 00:01:17,880
If I told her about her mother's actions...

18
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,450
She would be devastated.

19
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:28,070
We found no evidence against Sayaka's mother.

20
00:01:30,570 --> 00:01:35,640
It's best we keep this on the down-low.

21
00:01:36,660 --> 00:01:40,010
You make a point.

22
00:01:43,140 --> 00:01:48,360
I'm sorry. I said we ought to be cautious,

23
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:51,450
yet I went and ran my mouth back there.

24
00:01:51,450 --> 00:01:54,100
Don't let it bother you.

25
00:01:55,080 --> 00:02:01,440
I also have a bucket load of complaints
I could make about that mother of hers.

26
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:04,510
But I made you take my side.

27
00:02:05,670 --> 00:02:12,910
You defended my education, and upbringing.

28
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:22,450
I was honestly a bit surprised.

29
00:02:27,310 --> 00:02:29,310
Still, I appreciated the support.

30
00:02:30,190 --> 00:02:33,600
Thank you.

31
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:42,150
I was only stating the obvious.

32
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,590
See you around.

33
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:53,150
See you.

34
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,730
Hayashida!

35
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:11,920
I forgot I still had Sayaka's albums.
[2019 High School Album]

36
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:21,860
Since we have them,
could you make that slideshow after all?

37
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:28,200
Sure thing.

38
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,820
Thanks.

39
00:03:34,610 --> 00:03:37,250
We also need a photographer on the day of...

40
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:40,690
I already planned to be there.

41
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:43,870
Thank you.

42
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:46,760
Then I'll see you at the ceremony.

43
00:03:51,130 --> 00:03:53,220
Sakuraba, wait!

44
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:59,920
Look.

45
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:09,430
You're the only reason
I found out as much as I did.

46
00:04:11,740 --> 00:04:14,650
Seriously, thanks for everything.

47
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:20,140
I'm glad I could help.

48
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:36,040
I suppose we call it here?

49
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,590
Yeah.

50
00:04:43,490 --> 00:04:49,720
<i>This was how our case came to a close.</i>

51
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:53,320
<i>From now on...</i>

52
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:57,960
<i>I vow to live solely for Sayaka's sake.</i>

53
00:05:05,910 --> 00:05:08,730
Where should we go today?

54
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:13,110
I'm fine going anywhere,
so long as you're with me.

55
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,350
Sayaka, here. It's going to be cold today.

56
00:05:16,350 --> 00:05:18,410
Thanks.

57
00:05:18,410 --> 00:05:20,040
♫ ♫

58
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:20,960
♫ ♫

59
